<D>__{west... southwest, captain mendez...}
<C>__{mendez }
<D>__{steady as she goes...}
<A>__{columbus walks over to fernando, who is leaning against the rail. he is smoking a cigar... as the smoke blows over fernando's face, fernando wretches... it's clear he's feeling seasick, trying to control it. columbus leans against the rail next to him, staring out at the darkness. then looks at his son again. fernando won't give in to the sickness, but columbus knows he'd feel better if he did.}
<C>__{columbus}
<D>__{how are you feeling, fernando?}
<C>__{fernando}
<P>__{(in a strangled voice)}
<D>__{not bad.}
<A>__{columbus nods meditatively, puffs out some smoke. fernando winces, gags slightly.}
<C>__{columbus}
<P>__{(almost casually)}
<D>__{you know what i always used to do?}
<A>__{fernando shakes his head.}
<C>__{columbus}
<D>__{swallow a piece of pork fat on a string. it always worked.}
<A>__{at the thought of the pork fat, fernando jerks his head over the side, and vomits copiously. columbus smiles, pats him on the back.}
